"**Considering threading implementation**\\\\n\\\\nI want to think about using Future blocking, but I should avoid being too broad in my approach. One option could be to use `java.util.concurrent.Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor` and submit tasks to it. But then I need to consider whether to close the server or start a new thread. Additionally, there's a potential issue to look into: the Native Image might not include `javax.net` for SSL ALPN reflection. I'll need to investigate this further!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering testing dependencies**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about adding a test, and I might need some dependencies like `akka-actor-typed`. I can import `akka.actor.ActorSystem`, though I’m not sure if `akka.stream.Materializer` is necessary. I should consider setting up the actor system configuration to disable coordinated shutdown—it's important to ensure everything is properly terminated or bounded. Now, let’s get started on writing this!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_oDfntQsyp4lr0eeqq6zXRjzh|fc_04a73ab565b108c60169fc6d3de0c4819fab206683da6000e9\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-http-core_3/10.6.0-M1/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_http_core_3/Http2AlpnSupportTest.scala\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_typesafe_akka.akka_http_core_3\\n\\nimport akka.Done\\nimport akka.actor.ActorSystem\\nimport akka.http.scaladsl.Http\\nimport akka.http.scaladsl.model.HttpRequest\\nimport akka.stream.scaladsl.Sink\\nimport akka.stream.scaladsl.Source\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\n\\nimport java.net.InetAddress\\nimport java.net.ServerSocket\\nimport java.net.Socket\\nimport java.util.concurrent.CountDownLatch\\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit\\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference\\nimport scala.concurrent.Await\\nimport scala.concurrent.Future\\nimport scala.concurrent.duration.DurationInt\\nimport scala.util.control.NonFatal\\n\\nclass Http2AlpnSupportTest {\\n  @Test\\n  def http2TlsClientInitializesJdkAlpnSupport(): Unit = {\\n    val previousJavaSpecificationVersion: String = System.getProperty(\\\"java.specification.version\\\")\\n    System.setProperty(\\\"java.specification.version\\\", \\\"1.8\\\")\\n\\n    val system: ActorSystem = ActorSystem(\\\"http2-alpn-support-test\\\")\\n    val serverSocket: ServerSocket = new ServerSocket(0, 1, InetAddress.getLoopbackAddress)\\n    val acceptedConnection: CountDownLatch = new CountDownLatch(1)\\n    val serverFailure: AtomicReference[Throwable] = new AtomicReference[Throwable]()\\n\\n    val serverThread: Thread = new Thread(() => {\\n      try {\\n        val socket: Socket = serverSocket.accept()\\n        acceptedConnection.countDown()\\n        socket.close()\\n      } catch {\\n        case NonFatal(error) => serverFailure.set(error)\\n      }\\n    }, \\\"http2-alpn-support-test-server\\\")\\n    serverThread.setDaemon(true)\\n    serverThread.start()\\n\\n    try {\\n      val request: HttpRequest = HttpRequest(uri = \\\"/\\\")\\n      val response: Future[Done] = Source\\n        .single(request)\\n        .via(Http(system).connectionTo(\\\"127.0.0.1\\\").toPort(serverSocket.getLocalPort).http2())\\n        .runWith(Sink.ignore)(system)\\n\\n      try Await.result(response, 10.seconds)\\n      catch {\\n        case NonFatal(_) => ()\\n      }\\n\\n      assertTrue(acceptedConnection.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS), \\\"HTTP/2 TLS client should open a local TCP connection\\\")\\n      val failure: Throwable = serverFailure.get()\\n      if (failure != null) throw failure\\n    } finally {\\n      serverSocket.close()\\n      serverThread.join(TimeUnit.SECONDS.toMillis(10))\\n 